ish Radio and Television Corporation |access-date=3 February 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200203152227/https://www.trtworld.com/turkey/turkish-plane-carrying-wuhan-evacuees-lands-in-ankara-33408 |archive-date=3 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"NYT-20200326\">{{cite news |last=McNeil, Jr. |first=Donald G. |title=The U.S. Now Leads the World in Confirmed Coronavirus Cases \u2013 Following a series of missteps, the nation is now the epicenter of the pandemic. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/26/health/usa-coronavirus-cases.html |date=26 March 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"guardian29032020\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/29/china-coronavirus-anti-foreigner-feeling-imported-cases |title='They see my blue eyes then jump back' \u2013 China sees a new wave of xenophobia |first1=Lily |last1=Kuo |first2=Helen |last2=Davidson |date=29 March 2020 |work=The Guardian}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"diario6April\">{{cite web |title=Espa\u00f1a registra un aumento del 47% en la mortalidad pero los expertos piden tiempo para relacionarlo con el coronavirus |url=https://www.eldiario.es/sociedad/Espana-registra-mortalidad-relacionarlo-coronavirus_0_1013849053.html |access-date=7 April 2020 |language=es |date=6 April 2020 |first=Oriol Sol\u00e9 |last=Altimira |first2=Ra\u00fal |last2=S\u00e1nchez}}</ref>\n</references></div>\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Sister project links|voy=2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic|c=category:COVID-19 pandemic|d=Q81068910|q=no|b=no|v=no|s=Category:COVID-19|m=no|mw=no|wikt=COVID-19|species=Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|n=Category:COVID-19}}\n{{Scholia}}\n\n===Health agencies===\n\n* [https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019 COVID-19] ([http://www.who.int/news-room/q-a-detail/q-a-coronaviruses Questions & Answers], [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLbpi6ZahtOH5PLTT1yfXxcxDsNM40N1uG instructional videos]) by the [[World Health Organization]]\n* [https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/novel-coronavirus-china COVID-19] ([http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/novel-coronavirus-china/questions-answers Q&A]) by the [[European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control]]\n* [http://en.nhc.gov.cn/antivirusfight.html COVID-19] by the [[China National Health Commission]]\n* [https://www.moh.gov.sg/covid-19 COVID-19] ([http://www.moh.gov.sg/covid-19/faqs Q&A]) by the [[Singapore Ministry of Health]]\n* [https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/index.html COVID-19] ([https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/about/index.html Q&A]) by the [[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|U.S. Centers for Disease Control]]\n* [https://www.cdc.gov/niosh/emres/2019_ncov.html Coronavirus Disease 2019] ([https://www.cdc.gov/niosh/docs/2018-130/pdfs/2018-130.pdf?id=10.26616/NIOSHPUB2018130 Q&A]) by the [[National Institute for Occupational Safety and Health]]\n\n===Directories===\n\n* [https://curlie.org/Health/Conditions_and_Diseases/Respiratory_Disorders/COVID-19/ COVID-19 Directory on Curlie]\n* [https://openmd.com/directory/covid-19 COVID-19 Resource Directory on OpenMD]\n\n===Data and graphs===\n\n* [https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/situation-reports/ Coronavirus disease (COVID-2019) situation reports] and [https://who.sprinklr.com/ map] by the World Health Organization\n* [https://www.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases] and [https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19 historical data] created by [[Lauren Gardner (scientist)|Lauren Gardner]] at [[Johns Hopkins University]]\n* [https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/publications-data/download-todays-data-geographic-distribution-covid-19-cases-worldwide Historical data about COVID-19 cases] published by the [[European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control|European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC)]]\n* [http://unwfp.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/42b8837bb25049b9b1f69a9555d55808 World Travel Restrictions] based on [[World Food Programme|WFP]] data\n* [https://covid.observer Coronavirus Observer] based on [[Johns Hopkins University]] data\n* [https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/ Covid-19 coronavirus pandemic] published by the [[worldometers.info|Worldometer]] website\n* [https://ourworldindata.org/coronavirus Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) Statistics and Research] published by the [[Our World in Data]] website\n* [https://covid19.healthdata.org/united-states-of-america COVID-19 Projections] for many different countries published by [[Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation]]\n* [https://sites.google.com/site/pandemicdata/ Historical data with additional computations and graphs in user-friendly spreadsheet format] created by [https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Dianelos Dianelos Georgoudis]\n* [https://gabgoh.github.io/COVID/index.html Epidemic Calculator]: Epidemiology simulator<!--referenced by https://medium.com/@tomaspueyo/coronavirus-the-hammer-and-the-dance-be9337092b56 , in turn endorsed by hundreds of experts https://medium.com/tomas-pueyo/coronavirus-articles-endorsements-fdc68614f8e3-->\n\n===Medical journals===\n\n* [https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jama/pages/coronavirus-alert Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19)] by [[JAMA (journal)|JAMA]]\n* [https://www.bmj.com/coronavirus Coronavirus: News and Resources] by [[BMJ (company)|BMJ Publishing Group]]\n* [https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center Novel Coronavirus Information Center] by [[Elsevier]]\n* [https://www.thelancet.com/coronavirus COVID-19 Resource Centre] by [[The Lancet]]\n* [https://www.springernature.com/gp/researchers/campaigns/coronavirus SARS-CoV-2 and COVID-19] by [[Nature (journal)|Nature]]\n* [https://www.nejm.org/coronavirus Coronavirus (Covid-19)] by [[New England Journal of Medicine]]\n* [https://novel-coronavirus.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/ Covid-19: Novel Coronavirus] by